WEBVTT

00:25.113 --> 00:26.156
Mm?

00:33.121 --> 00:34.873
Been a wonderful tournament.

00:38.252 --> 00:39.878
Shame it's all over.

00:43.340 --> 00:44.841
Home is...

00:48.804 --> 00:50.722
Ah, it's brutally dull.

00:53.600 --> 00:54.601
Hey.

00:56.270 --> 00:57.688
You could come with me.

00:59.731 --> 01:01.733
Yeah, we'll hunt and hawk and...

01:02.568 --> 01:04.193
sail, make merry.

01:04.277 --> 01:06.029
I'll sharpen that iron of yours
so you don't make

01:06.113 --> 01:08.282
such a grand fool of yourself next time.

01:10.075 --> 01:11.368
Have you ever been to Tarth?

01:11.451 --> 01:13.954
-The man is dying, my lord.
-Huh? What?

01:14.037 --> 01:17.207
His wounds, they have mortified.
It's beyond my abilities.

01:17.291 --> 01:18.750
Oh, the Others fucking geld me.

01:18.834 --> 01:22.879
Beyond your-- an itchy arsehole
is beyond your abilities, my friend.

01:22.963 --> 01:24.298
Begone, witch!

01:24.381 --> 01:26.967
-Fuck off with you.
-Yes, my lord. At once.

01:27.050 --> 01:30.012
Cunt. It's fine. You're fine.
He's a terrible maester.

01:32.139 --> 01:33.139
Look.

01:36.351 --> 01:40.480
Come with me to Storm's End,
and I will love you like a brother.

01:46.903 --> 01:48.322
Oh, cunt.

01:51.490 --> 01:52.701
And if not...

01:53.744 --> 01:56.955
well, fuck you,
I'll hate you like a brother.

02:03.503 --> 02:04.796
It's a fine offer, Lyonel.

02:07.591 --> 02:10.802
But all I do is bring pain and suffering
to those around me.

02:10.886 --> 02:13.347
You've done the realm a kindness.
You'll see that one day.

02:13.430 --> 02:15.515
The only good dragon is a dead dragon.

02:15.599 --> 02:16.892
Fucking gods!

02:18.352 --> 02:19.561
Baelor fought for me.

02:19.645 --> 02:21.813
He gave his fucking life.

02:21.897 --> 02:23.899
Can you speak of him
with a little respect, please?

02:23.982 --> 02:25.483
Fuck that, and fuck you!

02:26.735 --> 02:28.570
I fought for you.

02:28.654 --> 02:30.155
Hardyng, Beesbury,

02:30.238 --> 02:32.824
the fucking apple boy, we fought for you.

02:32.908 --> 02:36.620
Your prince fought for you
against men sworn to protect him.

02:36.703 --> 02:38.580
He risked nothing!

02:41.958 --> 02:44.127
And the gods don't favor a fraud.

02:49.132 --> 02:51.259
Then why have they favored me?

02:52.969 --> 02:54.721
This is not favor, this...

02:56.932 --> 02:58.183
This is mockery.

03:00.602 --> 03:02.479
There's a war coming.

03:02.562 --> 03:04.272
We could be a force, you and I.

03:06.400 --> 03:07.901
You'll consider it?

03:10.862 --> 03:13.782
Good! Caravan departs after the roast.

03:15.951 --> 03:18.203
Baelor of House Targaryen.

03:19.329 --> 03:21.289
Prince of Dragonstone.

03:22.290 --> 03:24.793
Heir apparent to the Iron Throne.

03:26.545 --> 03:28.547
Hand of King Daeron the Good.

03:29.631 --> 03:31.591
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

03:32.718 --> 03:35.345
and Protector of the Realm.

03:38.557 --> 03:39.891
May the gods keep him.

04:05.125 --> 04:06.501
My prince.

04:08.920 --> 04:10.505
Your father, he was...

04:12.591 --> 04:14.009
He was a great man.

04:14.092 --> 04:15.677
He died in my armor.

04:19.346 --> 04:22.392
Plenty of sons have died
in their father's armor.

04:25.979 --> 04:28.440
How many fathers have died in their son's?

04:33.445 --> 04:34.988
I could not say.

04:43.079 --> 04:44.331
He was still young.

04:46.833 --> 04:49.127
He had it in him to be a great king.

04:49.211 --> 04:51.755
The greatest since Aegon the Dragon.

04:57.219 --> 04:59.638
Why would the gods take him and leave you?

05:04.893 --> 05:06.520
I've wondered the same.

05:13.735 --> 05:15.320
Be gone with you, Ser Duncan.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.919
Ser Duncan. Dunk!

05:34.589 --> 05:36.675
I went by your camp,
but you weren't there.

05:37.759 --> 05:39.261
I started getting worried.

05:41.054 --> 05:42.639
You've come from Baelor's funeral?

05:44.474 --> 05:45.892
I can't believe you went.

05:46.893 --> 05:48.228
I thought I owed it to him.

05:53.900 --> 05:55.318
Everybody...

05:55.402 --> 05:58.113
everybody blames me for his death,
don't they?

06:01.867 --> 06:03.118
I don't.

06:21.636 --> 06:22.637
Okay.

06:30.103 --> 06:31.438
Steffon took my tent.

06:31.521 --> 06:33.899
Said I betrayed the family
by abandoning him.

06:35.150 --> 06:36.526
Can you believe that?

06:37.777 --> 06:39.070
Left with little else.

06:39.154 --> 06:40.739
I'm sorry, Raymun.

06:40.822 --> 06:43.158
No, don't be. He's just mad that he lost.

06:43.992 --> 06:45.410
First trial of seven in 100 years,

06:45.493 --> 06:48.371
and Lord Steffon Fossoway
got beat by his little cousin.

06:49.873 --> 06:52.751
Besides, it's better to be
an unripe green apple

06:52.834 --> 06:54.419
than a wormy red one.

07:00.008 --> 07:01.635
Suits you.

07:01.718 --> 07:03.553
I think I broke one of my cousin's ribs.

07:05.013 --> 07:06.139
Morning.

07:12.187 --> 07:13.313
Good morning.

07:13.396 --> 07:15.774
Ser Duncan, this is Rowan...

07:21.071 --> 07:22.489
of the Green Apple Fossoways.

07:24.574 --> 07:26.660
-Huh?
-My wife.

07:26.743 --> 07:28.912
Pleased to meet you, Ser Duncan.

07:30.330 --> 07:31.748
Oh! Right.

07:32.374 --> 07:34.709
Pleased to meet you too, Lady Rowan.

07:34.793 --> 07:36.252
She come and watched the trial.

07:36.336 --> 07:38.546
-Said I fought like a wild bull.
-Mm.

07:39.214 --> 07:40.799
And with all the grace of one.

07:48.348 --> 07:49.432
Ah.

07:49.516 --> 07:52.143
I had no squire to see to my wounds,

07:52.227 --> 07:54.479
and she offered to help me
out my armor and...

07:59.651 --> 08:01.945
Anyway, she said
I've got her with child now,

08:02.028 --> 08:04.155
so I figured we ought to get married.

08:07.450 --> 08:08.660
Feels like a boy.

08:09.577 --> 08:11.579
You hear that, Ser Duncan? A boy.

08:14.249 --> 08:16.209
That's...

08:19.045 --> 08:20.046
Ser Duncan.

08:21.047 --> 08:22.549
Prince Maekar demands a word.

08:23.550 --> 08:25.593
-You're to come with us.
-He's not going anywhere.

08:25.677 --> 08:27.804
-He's been through enough.
-It's fine.

08:34.561 --> 08:35.729
I'll be fine.

08:37.355 --> 08:38.481
Congratulations.

09:08.762 --> 09:10.972
I'm sending Aerion to the East.

09:13.516 --> 09:18.063
A few years in the Free Cities
may change him for the better.

09:26.362 --> 09:29.032
Some men will say
I meant to kill my brother.

09:31.826 --> 09:34.788
The gods know it is a lie,
but I will hear the whispers

09:34.871 --> 09:36.623
till the day I die.

09:38.291 --> 09:41.002
You swung the mace, m'lord.

09:43.713 --> 09:46.341
But it was for me Prince Baelor died.

09:47.342 --> 09:49.427
You will hear them whisper as well.

09:50.970 --> 09:52.514
The king is old.

09:53.848 --> 09:58.728
When he dies, each time
a battle is lost or a crop fails,

09:58.812 --> 10:01.439
the fools will say Baelor
would not have let it happen.

10:04.984 --> 10:06.945
But the hedge knight killed him.

10:10.115 --> 10:11.825
If I had not fought,

10:13.868 --> 10:16.121
you would have had my hand and foot.

10:18.748 --> 10:22.001
I sat under the tree this morning

10:23.169 --> 10:25.421
and I asked, could I have spared one?

10:31.636 --> 10:35.640
I mean, how can a foot
be worth a prince's life?

10:37.183 --> 10:39.561
And what answer does your tree give you?

10:47.235 --> 10:50.155
Every day at evenfall,

10:51.322 --> 10:54.826
Ser Arlan would say,
"I wonder what the morrow will bring."

10:57.829 --> 11:00.874
Mightn't it be that some morrow will come
when I'll have need of that foot,

11:00.957 --> 11:05.461
when the realm will need that foot
even more than a prince's life?

11:08.590 --> 11:10.175
Not bloody likely.

11:11.259 --> 11:14.012
The realm has as many
hedge knights as hedges.

11:23.104 --> 11:26.107
My youngest son seems
to have grown fond of you, ser.

11:27.442 --> 11:29.194
It is time he was a squire.

11:30.737 --> 11:34.032
But he tells me he will serve
no knight but you.

11:36.242 --> 11:39.412
He is an unruly boy,
as you will have noticed.

11:39.495 --> 11:40.872
He's a good lad.

11:40.955 --> 11:43.291
Just needs a stern hand, that's all.

11:46.252 --> 11:47.462
Will you have him?

11:50.924 --> 11:52.175
Me?

11:52.258 --> 11:54.427
There is a place for you at Summerhall.

11:56.221 --> 11:59.682
You'll swear your sword to me,
and Aegon can squire for you.

11:59.766 --> 12:02.018
While you train him,

12:02.101 --> 12:04.646
my master-at-arms
will finish your own training.

12:07.273 --> 12:10.735
Your Ser Arlan did all he could for you,
I have no doubt.

12:12.862 --> 12:14.906
But you still have much to learn.

12:23.665 --> 12:25.667
I beg your pardon, m'lord, I do.

12:29.921 --> 12:31.756
But I think I'm done with princes.

12:35.510 --> 12:36.511
Yeah.

12:57.490 --> 12:58.866
Were you spying?

13:02.870 --> 13:03.871
No.

13:13.589 --> 13:15.216
Are you in a lot of pain?

13:23.975 --> 13:26.144
-Ser?
-I can't, Egg.

13:28.313 --> 13:29.314
I'm sorry.

13:36.988 --> 13:39.324
Maybe you're not the knight
I thought you were.

14:00.636 --> 14:02.722
Have you heard this story before?

14:04.891 --> 14:06.100
Many times.

14:06.184 --> 14:07.977
From where?

14:10.396 --> 14:11.481
From you.

14:12.315 --> 14:13.316
Oh.

14:21.616 --> 14:24.577
-May I ask you, ser--
-When a lord calls his banners

14:24.660 --> 14:27.622
and sends us boys off to war,

14:27.705 --> 14:30.416
it's custom for each to nail a penny

14:30.500 --> 14:33.169
to the oak in the square.

14:34.170 --> 14:37.006
And if we return, to take it down.

14:38.341 --> 14:40.343
Oh, it's a great oak tree.

14:41.761 --> 14:43.429
And yet,

14:43.513 --> 14:48.184
it's often hard to find
a spare bit to nail a new penny.

14:53.398 --> 14:55.775
Why did you never knight me?

14:58.236 --> 14:59.862
Did you think I'd leave you?

15:02.323 --> 15:03.658
I wouldn't have.

15:08.413 --> 15:10.081
Or was it something else?

15:16.087 --> 15:17.088
Ser?

15:22.301 --> 15:23.302
Ser?

15:29.934 --> 15:30.977
Ser?

15:55.293 --> 15:58.920
And that's why they call it
the Pennytree.

16:01.507 --> 16:06.304
A true knight always finishes a story.

16:10.099 --> 16:11.976
-To Beesbury.
-And to Hardyng.

16:12.810 --> 16:14.937
-To their memory.
-To the brave hearts.

16:16.022 --> 16:17.773
How do they get the bees
to swarm like that?

16:21.235 --> 16:23.321
Some sort of magic?

16:23.404 --> 16:24.405
Magic?

16:25.406 --> 16:26.616
What?

16:26.699 --> 16:28.451
Well, they put the queen
in Beesbury's coffin.

16:30.953 --> 16:32.288
Oh!

16:32.371 --> 16:35.458
Fucking bee magic.
My poor sweet warrior.

16:35.541 --> 16:38.085
All that fighting's turned
your brains to applesauce.

16:45.343 --> 16:48.137
-Do you yield, dragon whore?
-Eat shit, Sarrah!

16:48.221 --> 16:50.723
Serving boy! My cup.

17:10.993 --> 17:12.995
Have you no shame coming here?

17:15.540 --> 17:17.917
Those men are dead because of you.

17:24.966 --> 17:26.551
Will you take Egg to squire?

17:31.472 --> 17:32.640
I told your father.

17:34.058 --> 17:35.434
He's not my concern.

17:37.228 --> 17:39.188
You know...

17:39.272 --> 17:41.899
My brother wasn't always
such a little monster.

17:43.609 --> 17:44.944
Egg is no monster.

17:45.861 --> 17:46.862
He's just a boy.

17:46.946 --> 17:48.364
I didn't mean Egg.

17:48.447 --> 17:51.617
But no doubt we'll make a man of him, too.

17:55.246 --> 17:59.250
Perhaps the seeds of madness
are sown in the womb, as the maesters say.

18:02.378 --> 18:04.463
But Aerion was quite the glad child once.

18:05.715 --> 18:07.258
He liked fishing.

20:08.713 --> 20:10.297
What?

20:10.381 --> 20:13.300
Ser Duncan, my lord, requests an audience.

20:28.858 --> 20:31.777
I want you to know I do not blame you
for ruining my name day.

20:31.861 --> 20:35.489
It was a rotten thing they've done to you,
and you were right in your reply.

20:38.576 --> 20:39.577
Thanks.

20:46.959 --> 20:49.837
Speak quick. I'm near rid of this place.

20:50.963 --> 20:52.465
Before your brother died,

20:52.548 --> 20:54.425
he said the realm needed good men.

20:54.508 --> 20:55.676
What of it?

20:56.886 --> 20:58.512
I will take Egg to squire.

21:00.097 --> 21:01.474
But not at Summerhall.

21:03.434 --> 21:05.603
I thought you were done with princes.

21:05.686 --> 21:06.979
Egg is no prince.

21:07.980 --> 21:08.981
Not yet.

21:10.900 --> 21:14.069
Might be he's better served
away from castles,

21:14.153 --> 21:16.614
-and servants, and--
-His family?

21:22.703 --> 21:24.288
If you would consent...

21:25.956 --> 21:28.209
I would bring him on the road with me.

21:29.084 --> 21:30.711
He'll learn to squire as I did.

21:31.712 --> 21:34.924
We'll sleep in inns, stables.

21:36.926 --> 21:40.638
Now and again, in the halls
of some landed knight

21:40.721 --> 21:42.139
or lesser lordling.

21:44.850 --> 21:46.811
Maybe under a tree, when we must.

21:46.894 --> 21:49.688
I forbid him to live as a peasant.

21:50.397 --> 21:52.274
Aegon is blood of the dragon.

21:53.400 --> 21:57.780
He cannot sleep in ditches
and eat hard salt beef.

22:02.034 --> 22:03.911
Daeron never slept in a ditch.

22:06.872 --> 22:09.083
And all the beef Aerion ever ate was

22:10.167 --> 22:11.794
thick and rare and bloody.

22:23.138 --> 22:25.182
He's my last son.

22:47.788 --> 22:49.164
Sweetfoot!

22:53.919 --> 22:55.087
What are you doing here, girl?

22:59.383 --> 23:01.844
I hear Ser Lyonel wants you for a stag.

23:01.927 --> 23:04.096
Storm End's a sad place.

23:04.179 --> 23:06.223
Figured an old friend
might brighten it up for you.

23:09.393 --> 23:11.186
You bought me a horse?

23:16.317 --> 23:17.776
I won't be going with Lyonel.

23:20.613 --> 23:22.281
What will you do then?

23:22.364 --> 23:23.741
What I should have done all along.

23:25.326 --> 23:27.077
Ride her in the other direction.

23:29.288 --> 23:31.248
What about you?

23:31.332 --> 23:33.042
I don't know.

23:33.125 --> 23:36.378
Father always spoke about
building up the cider business,

23:36.462 --> 23:38.672
opening a new barreling outfit.

23:40.215 --> 23:41.216
Cider?

23:42.885 --> 23:46.138
Well, you should have your
Sweetfoot back, in any matter.

23:51.769 --> 23:52.895
She's not mine.

23:54.271 --> 23:55.314
Not anymore.

23:58.817 --> 23:59.818
Besides...

24:01.195 --> 24:02.988
I think an orchard might suit her better.

24:04.490 --> 24:06.325
What?

24:06.408 --> 24:07.868
I can't.

24:09.370 --> 24:10.454
Are you certain?

24:12.289 --> 24:14.291
She is a fine animal.

24:16.210 --> 24:18.879
Hello there, Sweetfoot.
Do you like apples?

25:50.095 --> 25:52.389
I don't know, Chestnut. Stop asking me.

25:55.726 --> 25:57.770
Where would the old man go? Hm?

26:04.443 --> 26:05.319
Ser Duncan!

26:09.740 --> 26:11.700
My lord father says I am to serve you.

26:21.502 --> 26:24.088
"Serve you, ser."

26:25.631 --> 26:28.217
Chestnut's yours. Treat her kindly.

26:29.635 --> 26:32.513
And I don't want to find you on Thunder
unless I put you there.

26:35.057 --> 26:36.517
Where are we going, ser?

26:37.976 --> 26:38.977
Don't know.

26:40.813 --> 26:42.856
I suppose we could go anywhere
in the Seven Kingdoms,

26:42.940 --> 26:44.358
-though I've never been to D--
-Nine.

26:46.860 --> 26:49.863
-What?
-There are nine kingdoms, ser.

26:50.989 --> 26:53.408
-Of what?
-The realm.

26:55.410 --> 26:56.703
Are you mad?

26:56.787 --> 26:58.247
Is that relevant?

26:58.330 --> 27:00.624
There are seven kingdoms
of the realm, boy.

27:00.707 --> 27:02.126
Everyone knows that.

27:02.209 --> 27:05.003
-Then, everyone is wrong.
-Do you want a clout in the ear?

27:05.087 --> 27:08.090
Crownlands, Westerlands,
Stormlands, Riverlands,

27:08.173 --> 27:10.467
the Iron Islands, the North, the Reach,

27:10.551 --> 27:12.427
the Vale of Arryn, and Dorne.

27:16.640 --> 27:18.475
No, but...

27:18.559 --> 27:21.395
I've never been over
the Red Mountains before.

27:21.478 --> 27:23.730
I hear they have
good puppet shows in Dorne.

28:20.454 --> 28:21.663
Hyah! Hyah!

28:25.876 --> 28:28.212
-Where's Aegon?
-I've not seen him, my prince.

28:28.295 --> 28:29.880
I will ask the septons.

28:32.966 --> 28:34.426
Where the fuck is he?!
